Task:
Raghu is a shoe shop owner. His shop has X number of shoes.He has a list containing the size of each shoe he has in his shop.There are
N number of customers who are willing to pay x(i) amount of money only if they get the shoe of their desired size.Your task is to compute
how much money Raghu earned.
Program:
from collections import Counter
# Input number of shoes and sizes
X = int(input())
sizes = Counter(map(int, input().split()))
# Input number of customers
N = int(input())
total_earned = 0
for _ in range(N):
    size, price = map(int, input().split())
    # Check if size is available
    if sizes[size] > 0:
        total_earned += price
        sizes[size] -= 1
print(total_earned)
